[ctns_make id='LF-XInterceptS']

    [ctns_front]
X-Intercept<br/>Linear Function
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
The $$x$$-intercept of a function is the value of $$x$$ when $$y=0$$. 
    [/ctns_back]
    
    [ctns_frontspeak]
The x-intercept -- linear function.
    [/ctns_frontspeak]

    [ctns_backspeak]
The x-intercept of a function is the value of x when y equals 0.
    [/ctns_backspeak]

[/ctns_make]
